Vienna, 30th October 1937
Dear Sir;
As I have to work on the theme: " Technic and Idea of Sherw. Andersons Works" at the Vienna University I thought of applying to your kindness for some informations. I therefore jotted down a few sentences to be corrected afterwards and this scrap of paper by some mistake was posted and will be or is in your hands. I dearly hope and wish, that you will excuse these rush and unmeditated expressions. In Vienna I could get hold only of four of your books: A Story Tellers Story; Triumph of the Egg, Dark Laughter and Poor White. I am told the books are too expensive for our libraries. Perhaps you may be so kind to
